New Records: Harry Kane scored twice on his 100th appearance for England.
Harry Kane became the first player since Wayne Rooney to reach 100 caps.
Harry Kane scored his 26th and 27th goals in 35 appearances at Wembley.
Lee Carsley achieved his first two competitive wins as England manager with a clean sheet.
Angel Gomes became the first player to start for England while playing for a French club since 1992.
Key Match Events: Harry Kane scored the first goal after a disallowed header in the first half.
Kane scored again in the second half with a brilliant finish.
Lukas Hradecky made several key saves for Finland.
Pre-Game Insights: The match was highlighted by England's fluid play and Finland's defensive strategy.
Post-Match Reflections: Harry Kane reflected on his journey from loan spells to his 100th cap.
Noni Madueke expressed pride in his debut and assist for Kane's goals.
Lee Carsley discussed the team's evolving style and preparation.
Miscellaneous Highlights: England secured their 10th victory in 12 meetings with Finland.
Harry Kane wore golden boots to mark his 100th appearance.
